A cannabis growhouse and drugs worth €200,000 were discovered during a search of a premises in the Co Westmeath village of Tyrrellspass on Thursday evening. Following a tip off from the public about suspicious behaviour in the vicinity of a disused petrol station in Tyrrellspass, gardaí entered the property and discovered approximately 260 cannabis herb plants with an estimated street value of around €200,000. The seizure is one of the biggest in the Mullingar Garda District in recent years. A Garda spokesperson said that the investigation was ongoing and appealed to members of the public who may noticed anything suspicious in the Tyrrellspass area in the last number of weeks to contact Mullingar Garda Station.